eb | title=Valmiki Dharam Samaj launches welfare plan | website=Tribune News Service | date=2017-10-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/ludhiana/valmiki-dharam-samaj-launches-welfare-plan/476483.html | access-date=2018-07-30}}</ref>
==Beliefs== [[File:Balmiki.jpg|right|thumb|Valmiki Temple]] [[File:Balmiki jayanti.jpg|right|thumb|Pargat Diwas of Lord Valmiki]] Followers believe that Valmiki's teachings and they consider his works, the ''[[Ramayana]]'' and the ''[[Yoga Vasistha]]'', as their holy [[scripture]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.speakingtree.in/blog/the-first-poet-of-universe|title=The First Poet of Universe|website=www.speakingtree.in|access-date=2018-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.in/Valmiki-Ramyana-Prof-P-P-S-Sastri/dp/8185170177|title=Valmiki Ramyana|last=Prof.P.P.S.Sastri|date=1983-01-01|publisher=The Kuppuswami Sastigal Research Institute/Chennai|isbn=9788185170176|edition=Sixth|language=English}}</ref> The community has their exclusive temples having only portraits and statues of Lord Valmiki.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Jagpal|date=1998|title=Ambedkarisation and Assertion of Dalit Identity: Socio-Cultural Protest in Meerut District of Western Uttar Pradesh|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/4407245|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|volume=33|issue=40|pages=2611–2618}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2015-06-05|title=Ambedkarisation and Assertion of Dalit Identity-Socio-Cultural Protest in Meerut District of Western Uttar Pradesh|url=https://www.epw.in/journal/1998/40/special-articles/ambedkarisation-and-assertion-dalit-identity-socio-cultural-protest|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|language=en|volume=33|issue=40}}</ref> [[Shambuka]] is considered as victim of [[Caste system in India|caste discrimination]] by the community members.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=f-1HDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT303&lpg=PT303&dq=Valmikism&source=bl&ots=h6_QSsbkib&sig=-jcTW6L3GmGB1DNNk9oZFeGwH1g&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwitoK-7-8bcAhWKpo8KHYnwCeE4ChDoATAGegQIBhAB#v=onepage&q=shambuk&f=false|title=Authority and Meaning in Indian Religions: Hinduism and the Case of Valmiki|last=Leslie|first=Julia|date=2017-11-22|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781351772983|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/opinion/jai-bhim-not-ram-223605|title=Jai Bhim, not Ram|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-07-30|language=en}}</ref>
