'''Irreligion in South Korea''' is common, with 56% percent of the population saying they are not affiliated with a religion, as of the 2015 national census.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://kosis.kr/statHtml/statHtml.do?orgId=101&tblId=DT_1PM1502&conn_path=I2|title=성, 연령 및 종교별 인구 - 시군구|last=|first=|date=2015|website=Korean Statistical Information Service|language=ko|trans-title=Population by Gender, Age, and Religion - City/Country|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-03-17}}</ref> [[South Korea]] also has the 5th largest population of [[Atheism|atheists]] in the world, according to a 2012 [[WIN/GIA|Gallup International]] poll, which found that 15% of South Koreans were "convinced atheists."<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/136318147/Win-gallup-International-Global-Index-of-Religiosity-and-Atheism-2012|title=Global Index of Religiosity and Atheism|last=|first=|date=2012-07-27|work=WIN-Gallup International|access-date=2018-03-20|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
